Uber data analysis by MYSQL & power bi

Sql queries
Q1. Retrieve all successful booking
ANS. Create View Successful as SELECT*FROM BOOKING WHERE BOOKING_STATUS= ‘SUCCESS’;
 Q2. Find the average ride distance for each vehicle type
ANS. SELECT VECHILE_TYPE, AVG(RIDE_DISTANCE) AS AVG_DISTANCE FROM BOOKING GROUP BY VEHICLE TYPE;
Q3. Get the total no. of canceled rides by customers
ANS. CREATE VIEW CANCLED_RIDES_BY_CUSTOMER AS SELECT COUNT(*) FROM BOOKING WHERE BOOKING_STATUS = ‘CANCELED_BY_CUSTOMER’;
Q4. List the top 5 customers who booked the highest no. of rides
ANS. CREATE VIEW TOP 5 AS SELECT CUSTOMER_ID ,COUNT(BOOKING_ID)AS TOTAL_RIDES FROM BOOKING GROUP BY CUSTOMER_ID ORDER BY TOTAL_RIDES DESC LIMIT 5;
Q5. Get the no. of rides canceled by drivers due to personal & car-related issues
ANS. CREATE VIEW CANCEL_BY_DREIVER_PERSONAL_ISSUES AS SELECT COUNT(*) FROM BOOKINNG WHERE CANCELED_RIDES_BY_DRIVERS= ‘Personal & car related issues’;
Q6. Find max & min driver rating for Prime Sedan bookings
ANS. CREATE VIEW MAX & MIN AS SELECT MAX(DRIVER_RATINGS),MIN(DRIVER_RATINGS) FROM BOOKING WHERE VEHICLE_TYPE= ‘Prime Sedan’;
Q7. Retrieve all rides where payment was made using UPI.
ANS. CREATE VIEW UPI AS SELECT* FROM BOOKING  WHERE PAYMENT_METHOD = ‘UPI’;
Q8. Find the average customer rating per vehicle type
ANS. CREATE VIEW CUSTOMER_RATING_WITH_VEHICLE_TYPE AS SELECT VEHICLE_TYPE, AVG(CUSTOMER_RATING) AS CUSTOMER_RATING FROM BOOKING GROUP BY VECHILE_TYPE;
Q9.  Calculate the total booking value of rides completed successful.
ANS. CREATE VIEW SUCCESSFUL_BOOKING AS SELECT SUM (BOOKING_VALUE) AS TOTAL_BOOKING_SUCCESSFUL FROM BOOKING WHERE BOOKING_STATUS= ‘SUCCESS’;
Q10. List all incomplete rides along with the reason.
ANS. CREATE VIEW INCOMPLE_RIDES_WITH_REASON AS SELECT BOOKING_ID, INCOMPLETE_RIDES_REASON, INCOMPLETE RIDES_REASON, INCOMPLETE_RIDES FROM BOOKING WHERE INCOMPLETE_RIDES= ‘YES’;
